{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-16",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_16_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Third Murder",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 520.72,
  "page_end_sec": 761.74,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.545,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 520.72,
      "end": 522.96,
      "text": "Those three came together while Brigid was there",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 523.52,
      "end": 526.86,
      "text": "and the five of them did a lot of talking in the Captain's cabin."
    },
    {
      "start": 527.96,
      "end": 529.58,
      "text": "It's hard to get anything out of the crew,"
    },
    {
      "start": 530.0,
      "end": 531.02,
      "text": "but they had a row"
    },
    {
      "start": 531.26,
      "end": 533.06,
      "text": "and somewhere around eleven o'clock"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.06,
      "end": 533.56,
      "text": "that night"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.64,
      "end": 536.02,
      "text": "a gun went off there, in the Captain's cabin."
    },
    {
      "start": 536.3,
      "end": 538.16,
      "text": "The watchman beat it down there,"
    },
    {
      "start": 538.3,
      "end": 538.66,
      "text": "but the"
    },
    {
      "start": 538.72,
      "end": 541.34,
      "text": "Captain met him outside and told him everything was all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 542.22,
      "end": 543.7,
      "text": "There's a fresh bullet-hole in one"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.78,
      "end": 544.6,
      "text": "corner of the cabin,"
    },
    {
      "start": 544.76,
      "end": 546.7,
      "text": "up high enough to make it likely that"
    },
    {
      "start": 546.7,
      "end": 548.14,
      "text": "the bullet didn't go through anybody"
    },
    {
      "start": 548.4,
      "end": 548.92,
      "text": "to get there."
    },
    {
      "start": 549.74,
      "end": 550.64,
      "text": "As far as I could learn"
    },
    {
      "start": 550.78,
      "end": 552.3,
      "text": "there was only the one shot."
    },
    {
      "start": 553.02,
      "end": 554.1,
      "text": "But as far as I could learn"
    },
    {
      "start": 554.44,
      "end": 555.12,
      "text": "wasn't very far.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 555.4,
      "end": 557.64,
      "text": "He scowled and inhaled smoke again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 558.08,
      "end": 558.62,
      "text": "\"Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.84,
      "end": 560.06,
      "text": "they left around"
    },
    {
      "start": 560.4,
      "end": 561.04,
      "text": "midnight—the Captain"
    },
    {
      "start": 561.1,
      "end": 562.62,
      "text": "and his four visitors all together—"
    },
    {
      "start": 562.88,
      "end": 565.38,
      "text": "and all of them seem to have been walking all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 566.2,
      "end": 566.42,
      "text": "I got"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.42,
      "end": 567.44,
      "text": "that from the watchman."
    },
    {
      "start": 568.26,
      "end": 569.84,
      "text": "I haven't been able to get hold of"
    },
    {
      "start": 569.84,
      "end": 571.78,
      "text": "the Custom-House-men who were on duty"
    },
    {
      "start": 571.88,
      "end": 572.3,
      "text": "there then."
    },
    {
      "start": 572.89,
      "end": 573.82,
      "text": "That's all of it."
    },
    {
      "start": 573.88,
      "end": 575.84,
      "text": "The Captain hasn't been back since."
    },
    {
      "start": 576.65,
      "end": 578.66,
      "text": "He didn't keep a date he had this"
    },
    {
      "start": 578.7,
      "end": 579.94,
      "text": "noon with some shipping-agents,"
    },
    {
      "start": 580.42,
      "end": 582.68,
      "text": "and they haven't found him to tell him about the fire."
    },
    {
      "start": 583.64,
      "end": 584.07,
      "text": "\"And the fire?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 584.26,
      "end": 585.02,
      "text": "she asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 585.984,
      "end": 586.7,
      "text": "Spade shrugged.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 586.78,
      "end": 587.72,
      "text": "\"I don't know."
    },
    {
      "start": 588.9,
      "end": 592.06,
      "text": "It was discovered in the hold, aft—in the rear basement—"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.2,
      "end": 592.96,
      "text": "late this morning."
    },
    {
      "start": 593.52,
      "end": 596.06,
      "text": "The chances are it got started some time yesterday."
    },
    {
      "start": 597.02,
      "end": 598.16,
      "text": "They got it out all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 598.56,
      "end": 599.72,
      "text": "though it did damage enough."
    },
    {
      "start": 600.736,
      "end": 603.02,
      "text": "Nobody liked to talk about it much while the Captain's away."
    },
    {
      "start": 603.3,
      "end": 604.02,
      "text": "It's the—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 604.02,
      "end": 605.92,
      "text": "The corridor-door opened.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 606.496,
      "end": 607.42,
      "text": "Spade shut his mouth."
    },
    {
      "start": 608.128,
      "end": 609.72,
      "text": "Effie Perine jumped down from the desk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 609.84,
      "end": 612.62,
      "text": "but a man opened the connecting door before she could reach it."
    },
    {
      "start": 613.376,
      "end": 613.86,
      "text": "\"Where's Spade?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 614.06,
      "end": 615.06,
      "text": "the man asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.9,
      "end": 618.72,
      "text": "His voice brought Spade up erect and alert in his chair.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 619.56,
      "end": 621.64,
      "text": "It was a voice harsh and rasping with agony"
    },
    {
      "start": 622.22,
      "end": 624.98,
      "text": "and with the strain of keeping two words from being smothered"
    },
    {
      "start": 625.0,
      "end": 627.82,
      "text": "by the liquid bubbling that ran under and behind them."
    },
    {
      "start": 628.96,
      "end": 629.42,
      "text": "Effie Perine,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 629.52,
      "end": 629.76,
      "text": "frightened,"
    },
    {
      "start": 629.92,
      "end": 631.08,
      "text": "stepped out of the man's way."
    },
    {
      "start": 631.74,
      "end": 633.82,
      "text": "He stood in the doorway with his soft hat",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 633.98,
      "end": 636.3,
      "text": "crushed between his head and the top of the door-frame:"
    },
    {
      "start": 636.82,
      "end": 638.1,
      "text": "He was nearly seven feet tall."
    },
    {
      "start": 638.61,
      "end": 641.64,
      "text": "A black overcoat cut long and straight and"
    },
    {
      "start": 641.64,
      "end": 644.06,
      "text": "like a sheath, buttoned from throat to knees,"
    },
    {
      "start": 644.26,
      "end": 645.96,
      "text": "exaggerated his leanness."
    },
    {
      "start": 646.38,
      "end": 647.72,
      "text": "His shoulders stuck out,"
    },
    {
      "start": 647.72,
      "end": 647.98,
      "text": "high,"
    },
    {
      "start": 648.14,
      "end": 648.32,
      "text": "thin,"
    },
    {
      "start": 648.54,
      "end": 650.6,
      "text": "angular. His bony face—"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.84,
      "end": 651.64,
      "text": "weather-coarsened,"
    },
    {
      "start": 651.78,
      "end": 652.4,
      "text": "age-lined—"
    },
    {
      "start": 653.04,
      "end": 655.42,
      "text": "was the color of wet sand and was wet with"
    },
    {
      "start": 655.5,
      "end": 656.72,
      "text": "sweat on cheeks and chin."
    },
    {
      "start": 657.86,
      "end": 659.58,
      "text": "His eyes were dark and bloodshot"
    },
    {
      "start": 660.22,
      "end": 663.6,
      "text": "and mad above lower lids that hung down to show pink inner"
    },
    {
      "start": 663.74,
      "end": 663.98,
      "text": "membrane."
    },
    {
      "start": 664.79,
      "end": 666.78,
      "text": "Held tight against the left side of his"
    },
    {
      "start": 666.78,
      "end": 669.6,
      "text": "chest by a black-sleeved arm that ended in a"
    },
    {
      "start": 669.82,
      "end": 673.58,
      "text": "yellowish claw was a brown-paper-wrapped parcel bound with thin rope—"
    },
    {
      "start": 674.26,
      "end": 675.66,
      "text": "an ellipsoid somewhat larger"
    },
    {
      "start": 676.26,
      "end": 677.32,
      "text": "than an American football."
    },
    {
      "start": 678.09,
      "end": 679.78,
      "text": "The tall man stood in the doorway",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 679.96,
      "end": 681.16,
      "text": "and there was nothing to show"
    },
    {
      "start": 681.36,
      "end": 682.66,
      "text": "that he saw Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 683.38,
      "end": 683.76,
      "text": "He said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 683.92,
      "end": 684.76,
      "text": "\"You know—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 685.76,
      "end": 688.288,
      "text": "and then the liquid bubbling came up in his throat and"
    },
    {
      "start": 688.68,
      "end": 690.12,
      "text": "submerged whatever else he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 690.68,
      "end": 693.72,
      "text": "He put his other hand over the hand that held the ellipsoid."
    },
    {
      "start": 694.656,
      "end": 696.06,
      "text": "Holding himself stiffly straight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 696.3,
      "end": 698.48,
      "text": "not putting his hands out to break his fall,"
    },
    {
      "start": 698.64,
      "end": 700.3,
      "text": "he fell forward as a"
    },
    {
      "start": 700.3,
      "end": 700.82,
      "text": "tree falls."
    },
    {
      "start": 701.1,
      "end": 701.2,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 702.4,
      "end": 703.68,
      "text": "wooden-faced and nimble,"
    },
    {
      "start": 703.8,
      "end": 706.22,
      "text": "sprang from his chair and caught the falling man."
    },
    {
      "start": 706.52,
      "end": 706.62,
      "text": "When"
    },
    {
      "start": 707.52,
      "end": 708.18,
      "text": "Spade caught him"
    },
    {
      "start": 708.26,
      "end": 711.0,
      "text": "the man's mouth opened and a little blood spurted out,"
    },
    {
      "start": 711.7,
      "end": 712.44,
      "text": "and the brown-wrapped"
    },
    {
      "start": 712.52,
      "end": 714.96,
      "text": "parcel dropped from the man's hands and rolled"
    },
    {
      "start": 714.96,
      "end": 717.4,
      "text": "across the floor until a foot of the desk stopped"
    },
    {
      "start": 717.7,
      "end": 717.86,
      "text": "it."
    },
    {
      "start": 718.76,
      "end": 719.82,
      "text": "Then the man's knees bent"
    },
    {
      "start": 719.94,
      "end": 721.26,
      "text": "and he bent at the waist"
    },
    {
      "start": 721.4,
      "end": 723.78,
      "text": "and his thin body became limber inside the"
    },
    {
      "start": 723.86,
      "end": 724.74,
      "text": "sheathlike overcoat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 725.504,
      "end": 727.22,
      "text": "sagging in Spade's arms so that Spade"
    },
    {
      "start": 727.22,
      "end": 728.76,
      "text": "could not hold it up from the floor."
    },
    {
      "start": 729.728,
      "end": 731.28,
      "text": "Spade lowered the man carefully until",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 731.28,
      "end": 733.32,
      "text": "he lay on the floor on his left side."
    },
    {
      "start": 733.56,
      "end": 734.78,
      "text": "The man's eyes—"
    },
    {
      "start": 735.02,
      "end": 735.86,
      "text": "dark and bloodshot,"
    },
    {
      "start": 736.32,
      "end": 737.36,
      "text": "but not now mad—"
    },
    {
      "start": 738.0,
      "end": 739.3,
      "text": "were wide open and still."
    },
    {
      "start": 740.2,
      "end": 741.92,
      "text": "His mouth was open as when blood"
    },
    {
      "start": 742.14,
      "end": 743.06,
      "text": "had spurted from it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 743.42,
      "end": 744.86,
      "text": "but no more blood came from it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 744.9,
      "end": 747.68,
      "text": "and all his long body was as still as the"
    },
    {
      "start": 747.68,
      "end": 748.5,
      "text": "floor it lay on."
    },
    {
      "start": 748.68,
      "end": 749.64,
      "text": "Spade said:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 750.48,
      "end": 751.16,
      "text": "\"Lock the door.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 752.1,
      "end": 752.96,
      "text": "While Effie Perrine,"
    },
    {
      "start": 753.14,
      "end": 754.0,
      "text": "her teeth chattering,"
    },
    {
      "start": 754.26,
      "end": 754.8,
      "text": "fumbled with"
    },
    {
      "start": 754.8,
      "end": 755.66,
      "text": "the corridor's lock,"
    },
    {
      "start": 755.9,
      "end": 757.72,
      "text": "Spade knelt beside the thin man,"
    },
    {
      "start": 757.98,
      "end": 759.48,
      "text": "turned him over on his back,"
    },
    {
      "start": 759.64,
      "end": 760.44,
      "text": "and ran a hand"
    },
    {
      "start": 760.52,
      "end": 761.74,
      "text": "down inside his overcoat."
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}